
Fork a process and send TS packets to its standard input

Usage: tsp -O fork [options] 'command'

Parameter:

  Specifies the command line to execute in the created process.

Options:

  -b value
  --buffered-packets value
      Windows only: Specifies the pipe buffer size in number of TS packets.

  --format name
      Specify the format of the output TS stream. By default, the format is a
      standard TS.
      Must be one of "M2TS", "TS", "autodetect", "duck".

  --help
      Display this help text.

  -n
  --nowait
      Do not wait for child process termination at end of input.

